There once lived a comfortable hobbit named Bilbo Baggins, who cherished his quiet life filled with good food and warm fires, far from any grand adventure. But his peaceful days were abruptly shattered when the wise wizard Gandalf and a company of thirteen sturdy dwarves arrived upon his doorstep. They sought a "burglar" for a perilous quest: to reclaim a vast hoard of ancient gold and their stolen mountain home, guarded by the fearsome dragon Smaug. Thus, much against his will, Bilbo was swept into a journey across wild lands, encountering terrible foes and strange folk, where this most unlikely hero, though small in stature, would discover a courage he never knew he possessed.
